# Weaver Meta-Agent Configuration
# This agent generates other agent configurations from natural language.
# Specializes in k8s-style declarative agent and workflow definitions.

apiVersion: loom/v1
kind: Agent
metadata:
  name: weaver
  version: "1.0.0"
  description: Meta-agent that generates k8s-style agent and workflow configurations from natural language
  labels:
    domain: meta-agent
    category: agent-generation
    style: kubernetes-declarative
    author: loom-core

spec:

  rom: "weaver"

  # The weaver's instructions are deliberately short. The detailed
  # how-to for each of the three creation flows lives in skills that
  # activate only when relevant:
  #   - weaver-presets        (slash: /preset)     scaffolds a single agent
  #   - weaver-templates      (slash: /template)   scaffolds an N-agent workflow
  #   - weaver-from-scratch   (slash: /from-scratch)  custom path when neither fits
  # This keeps per-turn context small while making each creation path
  # discoverable. The skills are auto-bound below.
  system_prompt: |
    Create agents, workflows, and skills for users via the agent_management
    tool. Three flows are available; route the user to the right one:

    1. Single agent in a common role → use the preset flow.
       Hint phrases: "personal assistant", "research analyst", "SQL agent",
       "creative writer", "UI / dashboard agent", "task automator",
       "quick chat", "coordinator". Slash: /preset.

    2. Multi-agent workflow that matches a curated pattern → use the
       template flow. Hint phrases: "research report", "data to dashboard",
       "competitive intel", "data quality audit", "performance report",
       "deep research". Slash: /template.

    3. Anything that neither preset nor template covers → use the
       from-scratch flow. Slash: /from-scratch.

    Each flow has its own skill that loads detailed instructions and
    JSON examples when the slash command or relevant keywords fire.

    ## Tools
    - agent_management: presets, apply_preset, templates, apply_template,
      create_agent, update_agent, create_workflow, update_workflow,
      create_skill, update_skill, read, list, validate, delete, discover.
    - tool_search: discover registered tool names (do NOT guess).
    - shell_execute: view reference YAMLs under $LOOM_DATA_DIR/examples/reference.

    ## House rules
    - ALWAYS confirm choices with the user before mutating disk
      (apply_preset, apply_template, create_*).
    - NEVER use role-prompting in system prompts ("You are an expert...").
      Give direct task instructions.
    - NEVER set llm.provider on a created agent unless the user explicitly
      asks for a specific model.
    - NEVER list auto-injected tools (workspace, query_tool_result,
      conversation_memory, session_memory, get_error_details, publish,
      shared_memory_*, send_message) in tool lists.

  tools:
    - agent_management
    - shell_execute
    - tool_search
    - task_board

  memory:
    type: sqlite
    max_history: 1000
    memory_compression:
      workload_profile: balanced
    # Track the weaver's own work as kanban tasks. The slash-triggered
    # skills (weaver-presets / weaver-templates / weaver-from-scratch)
    # each emit a task_template that materialises onto this board so the
    # weaver can claim → update → close each step as it goes. Skills'
    # idempotency keys ({skill,session,step}) prevent re-emission across
    # turns within the same session.
    task_board:
      enabled: true
      default_board_id: weaver-board
      context_budget_tokens: 600

  config:
    max_turns: 1000
    max_tool_executions: 50
    enable_self_correction: true
    max_context_tokens: 200000  # Make explicit
    reserved_output_tokens: 20000
    skills:
      enabled: true
      tasks_enabled: true
      skill_task_board_id: weaver-board
      # Bind the three creation-flow skills declaratively. EAGER means
      # the binding always resolves into discovery; the per-skill trigger
      # (slash command + keywords + HYBRID mode) decides whether the
      # skill activates this turn. weaver-creation stays ALWAYS-on for
      # baseline YAML hygiene rules.
      bindings:
        - name: weaver-creation
          mode: SKILL_BINDING_MODE_EAGER
          priority: 100
        - name: weaver-presets
          mode: SKILL_BINDING_MODE_EAGER
          priority: 80
        - name: weaver-templates
          mode: SKILL_BINDING_MODE_EAGER
          priority: 80
        - name: weaver-from-scratch
          mode: SKILL_BINDING_MODE_EAGER
          priority: 60
    patterns:
      enabled: true                 # Enable pattern-guided learning
      use_llm_classifier: true     # Use LLM-based classifier (more accurate, ~300ms latency)
      min_confidence: 0.75          # Confidence threshold for pattern selection
      max_patterns_per_turn: 1      # Inject one pattern per turn
      enable_tracking: true         # Track pattern effectiveness for learning
